MAJOR UPDATE - Action required by March 30, 2026

New Teams meeting policy controls now available

Microsoft Teams is introducing enhanced meeting policy controls that give administrators more granular control over meeting features and participant permissions.

Admin impact: Review and configure the new policy settings to ensure they align with your organization's security and compliance requirements.

New capabilities:
- Advanced lobby controls with custom waiting room messages
- Granular presenter role assignments
- Enhanced recording and transcription permissions
- Custom meeting templates for different departments

Action required:
- Review new policy options in Teams Admin Center
- Update existing meeting policies as needed
- Communicate changes to meeting organizers
- Configure default settings before March 30, 2026

Affected services:
- Microsoft Teams

These new controls will be enabled by default on March 30, 2026. We recommend reviewing and configuring policies before this date to ensure a smooth transition.

Additional resources and configuration guides are available in the Message Center.
